### 27) Mettaton (Box / EX / NEO variants)

- Location: Hotland / CORE (multiple encounters)
- Quick summary: Multi-form robot boss. Box = quiz show. EX = performance battle with ratings. NEO = Genocide scripted fight.
- Attacks / Behavior: EX form uses legs, bombs, heart-to-heart essay typing, ratings system. Box uses arms/bombs. NEO has single powerful attack.
- ACT / Spare: EX: boost ratings above 10000 or complete essay. NEO: scripted one-hit defeat.
- Implementation notes: Form-switching system. Ratings counter for EX. Essay minigame. NEO is cinematic scripted event.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Mettaton/In_Battle

---

### 28) Migosp

- Location: Ruins
- Quick summary: Small insect that becomes lonely when fought alone; can merge with other Migosps.
- Attacks / Behavior: Single insect fires small projectiles. When other Migosps are present, they can merge into larger forms with different patterns.
- ACT / Spare: Spare immediately if alone (becomes depressed). If in group, defeat others first or use specific ACTs.
- Implementation notes: State changes based on ally count. Merge mechanic creates combined entity. Solo variant has instant-spare condition.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Migosp

---

### 29) Migospel

- Location: Hard Mode (Ruins variant)
- Quick summary: Hard Mode version of Migosp with gospel-themed attacks and more aggressive patterns.
- Attacks / Behavior: Denser insect swarms, faster projectiles, and coordinated group patterns. Gospel music theme.
- ACT / Spare: Similar to Migosp but requires more effort. Group dynamics affect spare conditions.
- Implementation notes: Increased spawn density and speed versus normal Migosp. Group coordination logic for multi-enemy encounters.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Migospel

---

### 30) Moldbygg

- Location: Waterfall
- Quick summary: Large mold creature with vertical drop attacks and body-slam patterns.
- Attacks / Behavior: Vertical falling slime drops; body slam that creates splash projectiles on impact.
- ACT / Spare: Lie Down to make Moldbygg lie on you (stops attacking). Unhug to spare afterward.
- Implementation notes: Vertical spawners from top. Splash burst on collision. Lie Down ACT disables attacks and starts spare sequence.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Moldbygg

