### 36) Napstablook

- Location: Waterfall
- Quick summary: Depressed ghost with music-themed attacks and low damage output.
- Attacks / Behavior: Tear drops (slow vertical projectiles), hat attacks (falling hats), and lying down (unavoidable damage but minimal).
- ACT / Spare: Cheer repeatedly to encourage. Fight ends when Napstablook feels better (can't truly be defeated).
- Implementation notes: Slow projectiles with musical timing. Lying down is scripted guaranteed-hit but low damage. Encourage ACT advances spare counter.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Napstablook/In_Battle

---

### 37) Papyrus

- Location: Snowdin (boss)
- Quick summary: Skeleton boss with bone attacks and puzzle-like patterns. Memorable and merciful.
- Attacks / Behavior: Blue bone attacks (stand still), normal bones (dodge), bone walls with gaps, and "cool dude" special attack with rotating bones.
- ACT / Spare: Can spare immediately on any turn. Sparing or losing results in befriending. Never kills player (captures instead).
- Implementation notes: Blue/orange attack mechanics. Pattern-based bone attacks with clear safe zones. Capture mechanic at 0 HP instead of death.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Papyrus

---

