### 48) Toriel

- Location: Ruins (boss)
- Quick summary: Motherly boss with fire magic. Tries not to hurt player but uses powerful attacks.
- Attacks / Behavior: Fireball waves avoiding soul at low HP, hand swipe flames, wall fires creating safe corridors. Becomes easier as fight progresses.
- ACT / Spare: Spare repeatedly (takes many turns) while surviving. Having low HP makes her avoid hitting you. Using Butterscotch Pie helps.
- Implementation notes: Damage avoidance AI when player HP is low. Multi-phase with weakening patterns. Item interaction (pie). Spare counter requires ~10+ mercy attempts.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Toriel/In_Battle

---

### 49) Tsunderplane

- Location: Hotland
- Quick summary: Tsundere airplane with flying attack patterns.
- Attacks / Behavior: Swooping plane projectiles, angled bullet spreads in formation, and blushing heart bullets when flustered.
- ACT / Spare: Approach multiple times to make Tsunderplane blush and become spareable. Distance management affects behavior.
- Implementation notes: Swoop paths with fast lateral movement. Formation shooting with angled spreads. Approach counter tracks distance/intimacy for spare.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Tsunderplane

---

### 50) Undyne

- Location: Waterfall (boss) / Genocide variant
- Quick summary: Heroine with spear attacks and determination. Two forms: regular Undyne and Undyne the Undying (Genocide).
- Attacks / Behavior: Spear projectiles from all directions, moving spear barriers, and forced soul color (green = face attacks). Undying form is faster and denser.
- ACT / Spare: Regular: Run away during chase, then later spare via befriending sequence. Undying: Must defeat (no spare option).
- Implementation notes: Green soul mode (restricted movement, face attacks). Spear spawners with directional patterns. Undying has enhanced HP/speed/pattern density.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Undyne

---

### 51) Undyne the Undying (Genocide variant)

- Location: Genocide route (Waterfall/Bridge)
- Quick summary: Determination-powered form with extreme difficulty and unrelenting attacks.
- Attacks / Behavior: Continuous rapid spear volleys, minimal safe windows, rotating spear circles, and aggressive patterns with no breaks.
- ACT / Spare: Cannot be spared; must be defeated. Extremely high HP and defense.
- Implementation notes: High-performance projectile pooling required. Minimal downtime between patterns. Difficulty spike requires precise collision and input handling.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Undyne

---

### 52) Vegetoid

- Location: Ruins
- Quick summary: Vegetable enemy with edible projectile mechanic.
- Attacks / Behavior: Falling vegetable projectiles that normally damage. If player uses Eat ACT during attack, vegetables become green healing items.
- ACT / Spare: Dinner ACT can spare. Eating during attacks changes their projectiles to healing.
- Implementation notes: Projectile state toggle (damage↔heal) based on Eat ACT. Green color for healing bullets. Edible flag per projectile.
- Source: https://undertale.fandom.com/wiki/Vegetoid

